details:
Case 147 is an imported case involving a 64 year-old male Indonesian national who arrived in Singapore on 7 March.

He reported onset of symptoms on 3 March while he was in Indonesia. He had a fever when he arrived at Seletar Airport, and underwent a COVID-19 swab test at the checkpoint. He was conveyed by ambulance to National Centre for Infectious Diseases (NCID) on 7 March night, and subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 8 March morning.

Prior to hospitalisation, he mostly stayed at his rental apartment in the Oxley Road area.
